      "content": "wait i just checked the logs again and looking at the script results... it's actually stripping the write access needed for scaling and emergency rollbacks too. technically it's \"more secure\" but if a node fails while you're in read-only mode, you won't be able to fix it. \n\nhonestly, this is overkill. i'm gonna let the script finish the IAM cleanup, but i'm thinking we might need to spin up a separate break-glass service account with full admin rights just so we don't lose control of the cluster. do you have any thoughts on how we should set that up or should i just do it manually?",
